\ basic
[ 1 2 3 ] [ 4 5 6 ] concat .

\ either or both empty
[ ] [ 1 2 3 ] concat .
[ 1 2 3 ] [ ] concat .
[ ] [ ] concat .

\ self-concat: dup then concat doubles the array
[ 1 2 3 ] dup concat .

\ set source on either side: items in stored (sorted) order, result is an array
< 5 1 3 > [ 7 8 ] concat .
[ 0 ] < 5 1 3 > concat .
< 1 2 > < 3 4 > concat .

\ stack shape: ( a b -- ab )
9 [ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat .
.s

\ composes
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat size .
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat reverse .
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat 2 take .
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat 2 skip .

\ associativity (over three arrays)
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] concat [ 5 6 ] concat .
[ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] [ 5 6 ] concat concat .

\ failures
[ 1 2 3 ] 5 concat
5 [ 1 2 3 ] concat
[ 1 2 3 ] concat
concat

\ flatten-array: deep flatten of nested arrays; a flat array returns unchanged
[ 1 2 3 ] flatten-array .                      \ already flat -> as-is
[ [ 1 2 ] [ 3 ] [ 4 5 6 ] ] flatten-array .    \ array of arrays
[ 1 [ 2 3 ] 4 ] flatten-array .                \ mixed scalars and arrays
[ [ 1 [ 2 3 ] ] [ 4 ] ] flatten-array .        \ deeply nested
[ ] flatten-array .                            \ empty
5 flatten-array                                \ non-array argument errors
